-- RAK Ceramics says major shareholder to sell 30.6 pct stake 
-- By Praveen Menon
-- Tue Apr 29, 2014 02:12AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, April 29 (Reuters) - Ras Al Khaimah Ceramics <RKCE.AD> said on Tuesday that its founding shareholder had agreed to sell 30.6 percent of his stake in the company to Samena Limestone Co, a company incorporated under the laws of the Cayman Islands.

Sheikh Saud bin Saqr al-Qasimi, a member of the ruling family of Ras Al Khaimah, which is one of the seven United Arab Emirates, has agreed to sell 250 million shares in the company, RAK Ceramics said in a bourse statement.